        "response_text": "Found it. The problem is in `conftest.py:34` — the `mock_stripe` fixture is **function-scoped** but `event_loop` is **session-scoped**. When two async tests run in the same event loop iteration, the mock's `call_count` carries over from the previous test.\n\nThe fix is either:\n1. Make `mock_stripe` session-scoped and reset it in a `yield` fixture\n2. Or add `scope='function'` to `@pytest.fixture(loop_scope='function')` on the event loop\n\nOption 1 is cleaner. I'll run the tests 5 times first to confirm this is reproducible before patching.",
